cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with feature-based methods for vehicle localization using ground texture, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for feature extraction and matching, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with localization, which could be considered under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
